Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - This paper deals with the folding of origami material along creases, which can be seen as a geometric problem. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a linear time algorithm for finding minimum forcing sets, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The concept of forcing sets and their minimum size can be seen as a discrete mathematical problem. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) - This may seem like an unlikely category, but the paper mentions the soundness of the algorithm in terms of correctness and completeness. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss computational complexity, the problem of finding minimum forcing sets can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the scope of computational complexity.
